OpenLMI Project proof-of-concept
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

The aim of this repository is track the OpenLMI Project from 
http://fedorahosted.org/openlmi

This Fedora project brings technologies around DMTF standards and initiatives.

The folders are populated of examples in order to understand the DMTF 
technology in general, and the OpenLMI Project in particular.

Folders overview:

openlmi-poc
|
├── cli-tools-java --------------> CLI tools from OpenLMI Project using Java
├── openlmi-condor -----------------> Condor OpenLMI CIM provider
├── openlmi-openstack --------------> OpenStack OpenLMI CIM provider
└── cmpi-providers-libs ---------> Prove of concept of underlaying libraries 
    |				   used in OpenLMI Project
    ├── konkretcmpi -------------> Simple C CMPI compliant CIM Provider
    ├── pywbem ------------------> Simple Python CIM Client 
    └── sblim-cim-client-java ---> Simple Java CIM Client


Roadmap:

- CLI tools from OpenLMI Project in Java: The aim of this programming exercise is
  to get background in order to develop a J2EE frond end usign WBEM technology.

- Condor CMPI Provider: CIM Provider for Condor Scheduler based on cmpi-openpbs
from SBLIM/IBM implementation.

- OpenStack CMPI Provider.

- Kernel tunning CMPI Provider.


